The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Ottawa/Toronto, Oct. 24: Ford Motor said it would idle its Oakville plant in Ontario, Canada, from October 26-30 because of a shortage of transmission parts arising out of the labour dispute at Rico Auto in India. The recent labour unrest at Rico Auto Industries in Haryana has resulted in a shortage of parts from Rico, said Ford Canada spokesperson Lauren More. Ford manufactures the Ford Edge, Ford Flex and the Lincoln MKX at the plant.                             
	 New Delhi, Oct. 24: The government should include all central and state level indirect taxes into the proposed goods and services tax, industry chamber CII has said. The chamber favours consolidation of VAT, purchase tax, cess and surcharge, luxury tax as well as entry tax collected by municipalities, barring property tax.                             
	 Calcutta, Oct. 24: Subrata Biswas took over as chairman of Damodar Valley Corporation (DVC) with effect from October 14. Biswas, an IIT mechanical engineer, was the secretary of the firm since 2006 before taking over the post.                                                                                                                           
